{"key":"processedPost-11018084","value":{"id":11018084,"first":10981443,"last":11072848,"when":1252388928,"utime":"09/08/09 08:48 AM","content":"As said, side pinning isn't caused by light.&nbsp; It's caused by the gap around the edge which is a nice place for primordia to form.&nbsp; Don't pick the side pins until they're mature mushrooms.&nbsp; They won't rot.&nbsp; Using a plastic bag on the inside will prevent it, but if your substrate wants to pin there, it means it doesn't like conditions on top.<br />RR","title":"Re: Monotub - Side pinning"}}